'''Benedict Sandin''' (1918–1982) was an [[Iban people|Iban]] [[ethnologist]], [[historian]], and [[Curator]] of the [[Sarawak Museum]] in [[Kuching]], [[Sarawak]], [[Malaysia]]. He also served as Government Ethnologist to the Government of Sarawak.
