[[Category:History]]

'''Jean-François Barrière''' (12 May 1786 &ndash; 22 August 1868) was a [[France|French]] [[historian]]. He wrote about the [[French revolution]], most notably an annotated biography of [[Madame Roland]] entitled ''Memoirs de Madame Roland, Avec une Notice sur sa Vie, des Notes et des Eclaircissemens historiques par MM. Saint-Albin Berville et Jean-François Barrière'', edited and published in 1827 by [[Honoré de Balzac]].

Barrière served 18 years in the [[Préfecture]] of Paris, rising through the ranks to become division chief. He was removed from office and forced to retire following the [[Revolution of 1848]].

