'''Mieczysław Albert Maria Krąpiec''' [[Dominican Order|OP]] (born May 25, 1921 in Berezowica Mała near [[Ternopil]], dead May 8, 2008 in [[Lublin]]) – a [[Poland|Polish]] [[Roman Catholic]] [[priest]], [[philosopher]] ([[thomist]]), [[theologian]], humanist and [[social scientist]], the [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of [[Katolicki Uniwersytet Lubelski]] (1970-1983), the founder of the [[Thomism#Lublin Thomism|Lublin Philosophical School]], the initiator and president of the scientific committee of ''[[Powszechna Encyklopedia Filozofii]]''.
